CO2 emissions / Climate change – sustainable construction equipment:

Criterion description: The use of electric/hybrid machinery in construction is no longer a novelty in Europe. These machines constitute an innovative alternative to traditional construction equipment that runs on various types of fuel. The drive to adopt sustainable practices has intensified over the past decade, making electric/hybrid machines ecological alternatives.

The most important hybrid/electric machines considered by the contracting authority for fulfilling this criterion are: wheel loaders, compactors and excavators.

1. The contracting authority awards 5 points to bidders who commit, for the entire period of work execution, to use:
   a) 5 hybrid/electric wheel loaders;
   b) 2 hybrid/electric compactors;
   c) 2 hybrid/electric excavators.

2. The contracting authority awards 3 points to bidders who commit, for the entire period of work execution, to use:
   a) 3 hybrid/electric wheel loaders;
   b) 1 hybrid/electric compactor;
   c) 1 hybrid/electric excavator.

3. The contracting authority awards 1 point to bidders who commit, for the entire period of work execution, to use:
   a) 1 hybrid/electric wheel loader;
   b) 1 hybrid/electric compactor;
   c) 1 hybrid/electric excavator.

When presenting offers, in the technical proposal the bidder must submit a self‑declaration undertaking to meet this requirement and provide certificates/documents proving compliance, namely documents confirming that the bidder has at its disposal or access to the necessary machinery, installations and technical equipment for contract execution, specifying the type of equipment/machine, manufacturer, model, serial number and equipment number. These documents must also be provided by any associated bidder whose resources are taken into account for meeting the requirement.

(Additional note in section II.2.5 – Award criteria from the Instructions to bidders.)

