Demonstration of an appropriate methodology to ensure that the works are carried out to the required quality parameters (Quality Management Plan for the executed works): Technical component, evaluation factor. The requirement "Demonstration of an appropriate methodology to ensure that the works are carried out to the required quality parameters (Quality Management Plan for the executed works)" has three major reference points, each divided into sub‑factors that will be used by the evaluation committee when assessing the technical offer. The committee will assign scores and grades based on the guidelines below. Each grade corresponds to a point value: "very good" – 24 points, "good" – 16 points, "acceptable" – 8 points. Scoring algorithm:
1. Quality Management Plan for the executed works:
   a) presented in a general manner and does not reflect the specific characteristics of the work centre, not fully correlated with the execution methodology;
   b) identifies the level of involvement of responsible persons in the contractor’s organisational structure for quality control, but is not detailed;
   c) indicates that quality control is performed at all stages of documentation implementation;
   d) contains more than five inconsistencies between the execution schedule, performed activities/phases, responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and allocated resources.
   Grade: Acceptable/Satisfactory/Partially relevant – points awarded: a)‑2, b)‑2, c)‑2, d)‑2. Total points: 8.
2. Quality Management Plan for the executed works (improved):
   a) adapted to the specific characteristics of the work centre and correlated with the execution methodology;
   b) adequately shows the level of involvement of responsible persons in the contractor’s organisational structure and their individual contribution to quality control;
   c) contains minor inconsistencies (between 2 and 5) between the execution schedule, activities/phases, responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and resources allocated;
   d) provides an appropriate level of detail that facilitates understanding of the proposed quality management throughout all stages of documentation implementation.
   Grade: Good/Adequate – points awarded: a)‑4, b)‑4, c)‑4, d)‑4. Total points: 16.
3. In addition to the information in point 2, for the "Good"/"Adequate" grade:
   a) the activities/phases, responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and resources used are very well defined, demonstrating resource optimisation;
   b) the relationship between the execution schedule/phases, responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and resources used is realistic and conforms to the proposed methodology (fewer than two minor inconsistencies);
   c) the level and manner of involvement of responsible persons in quality control are realistic and very clearly defined.
   Grade: Very good/Exceptional – points awarded: Good/Adequate – 16 points plus a) 2 points, b) 4 points, c) 2 points.

