Pollution standard of equipment (NP): Technical component, points are awarded as follows:
For each dump truck the following points are assigned:
a) For NP – Euro 6, hybrid, electric – 25 pts;
b) For NP – Euro 5 – 20 pts;
c) For NP – Euro 4 – 15 pts;
d) For NP – Euro 3 – 10 pts;
e) For NP – Euro 2 and Euro 1 – 0 pts;
f) For NP – non-Euro – non‑conforming technical proposal, i.e., non‑Euro dump trucks are not accepted.

The technical component score is calculated using the following formula:
Score = (N1+N2+N3+N4+N5+N6) / T
Score – technical component points;
N1 – number of dump trucks with Euro 6, hybrid, electric emission standard multiplied by 25 pts;
N2 – number of dump trucks with Euro 5 multiplied by 20 pts;
N3 – number of dump trucks with Euro 4 multiplied by 15 pts;
N4 – number of dump trucks with Euro 3 multiplied by 10 pts;
N5 – number of dump trucks with Euro 2 multiplied by 0 pts;
N6 – number of dump trucks with Euro 1 multiplied by 0 pts;
T – total number of dump trucks with wheel formulas 4x4, 6x4, 8x4 used for snow‑clearing on national roads and highways, as specified in Annex 2A (maximum).
Points are awarded only for dump trucks with wheel formulas 4x4/6x4/8x4 used for snow‑clearing on national roads and highways, according to Annex 2A (maximum) of the tender specifications.
The score is calculated by rounding to two (2) decimal places.
Method of fulfillment:
To award points, supporting documents must be submitted for each proposed dump truck for the technical evaluation factor (vehicle identification cards, registration certificates, technical data sheets or other documents indicating the emission standard). If an offer includes more dump trucks than required by the contracting authority, the points will be calculated based on the trucks with the newest emission standard.
No intermediate points are awarded, and no points are given to dump trucks that do not provide supporting documentation.

