The minimum distance (km) by rail, calculated as the average of the rail distances between the axis of the main railway stations (CF) of destination for the broken‑stone wagons and the axis of the railway station serving the supplier's broken‑stone quarry. Destination railway stations: Cluj‑Napoca, Oradea, Satu Mare, Dej Calatori, Bistriţa, Sighetu Marmaţiei are the main estimated destinations for the stone shipments. The contracting entity awards points for offering the smallest possible distance, according to the provisions of this evaluation factor. The score for the evaluation factor "Technical component", with a weight of 20 % of the total award criterion, is a maximum of 20 points and shall be awarded as follows:
