Delivery term for the products: The maximum delivery period is 60 days. For a delivery period longer than 60 days, the offer will be declared non‑conforming. Calculation algorithm:
The score for the evaluation factor “Delivery term” shall be awarded as follows:
For the admissible offer with the shortest delivery period = 10 points.
For the remaining admissible offers, the score shall be calculated using the following formula:
Pdelivery(n) = Delivery period (min) / Delivery period (n) × 10, where:
Pdelivery(n): the score obtained by the admissible offer under evaluation;
Delivery period (min): the shortest among the delivery periods of the admissible offers, expressed in days;
Delivery period (n): the delivery period of the admissible offer under evaluation, expressed in days;
For an offer with a delivery term of 60 days from the issuance of the order, it is considered compliant but receives no points, this representing the fulfillment of the minimum requirement requested in the specification.

