Termen de garantie extinsa: Componenta tehnica
Ofertantul prezintă o declarație scrisă care detaliază perioada oferită și care atestă că se acoperă conformitatea bunurilor cu specificațiile contractului, inclusiv toate utilizările indicate. Prin termen de garantie extinsa se intelege garantie suplimentara de maxim 24 luni, peste durata de garantie solicitata prin Caietul de sarcini (min. 24 luni)., Punctajul pentru factorul “Termenul de garantie extinsa” in conformitate cu principiile DNSH, care faciliteaza investitiile durabile, asa cum sunt prezentate in Regulamentul (UE) 2020/852, cu o valoare de 10 de puncte din totalul de 100 de puncte si cu o pondere de 10% din totalul criteriului de atribuire, se vor acorda dupa cum urmeaza:
a) pentru oferta admisibila care acorda garantie in perioada de 36 luni(24 luni garantie obligatorie + 12 luni garantie extinsa) – se acorda 5 puncte;
b) pentru oferta admisibila care acorda garantie in perioada de 42 luni(24 luni garantie obligatorie + 18 luni garantie extinsa) – se acorda 7 puncte;
c) pentru oferta admisibila care acorda garantie in perioada de 48 luni(24 luni garantie obligatorie + 24 luni garantie extinsa) – se acorda 10 puncte;
Pentru termenul de garantie minim specificat in CS (24 luni) nu se acorda punctaj, fiind conditie de conformitate a ofertei. Perioada minima de garantie obligatorie este de 24 luni.

column10:
Extended warranty term: Technical component
The tenderer provides a written declaration detailing the offered period and certifying that the conformity of the goods with the contract specifications, including all indicated uses, is covered. By extended warranty term is meant an additional warranty of up to 24 months, beyond the warranty period requested in the Terms of Reference (minimum 24 months). The scoring for the factor “Extended warranty term” in accordance with the DNSH principles, which facilitate sustainable investments, as presented in Regulation (EU) 2020/852, with a value of 10 points out of a total of 100 points and a weight of 10% of the total award criteria, shall be awarded as follows:
a) for an admissible offer that provides warranty for a period of 36 months (24 months mandatory warranty + 12 months extended warranty) – 5 points are awarded;
b) for an admissible offer that provides warranty for a period of 42 months (24 months mandatory warranty + 18 months extended warranty) – 7 points are awarded;
c) for an admissible offer that provides warranty for a period of 48 months (24 months mandatory warranty + 24 months extended warranty) – 10 points are awarded;
For the minimum warranty term specified in the Specification (24 months) no points are awarded, as it is a condition of conformity of the offer. The minimum mandatory warranty period is 24 months.

column4:
Energy efficiency of monitors in the Desktop system: technical component. The score for the factor "Energy efficiency of monitors in the Desktop system" will be awarded as follows:
a) For the offer that presents all monitors in the Desktop system with the lowest consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode, the maximum allocated score is awarded;
b) For offers that present all monitors with the lowest consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode above the lowest offered, P(n) is calculated proportionally as follows:
P(n) = Minimum offered energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode / Offered energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode × 5 points, where:
P(n) – score for the offered equipment n;
Minimum offered energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode – the lowest energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode among the offered equipment that meets the minimal requirements in the specification;
Offered energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) mode – the energy consumption in Standby (Inactive) for the offered equipment.

column3:
