column4:
Energy efficiency of the equipment: Any appropriate evidence will be accepted, for example:
- technical data sheet of the product / a technical dossier from the manufacturer;
- certificate of conformity;
- a testing report from a recognized body;
- any other relevant document that justifies the equipment's energy efficiency.

A simple declaration by the bidders regarding the energy efficiency of the offered equipment is not sufficient.

Note: The lowest energy consumption expressed in kWh/100 km accepted by the contracting authority is 5 kWh/100 km. Offers that contain values below 5 kWh/100 km will not receive additional points and will not be considered in the scoring calculation for this factor. The maximum score of 15 points is awarded to the offer that presents the lowest energy consumption expressed in kWh/100 km.

For the remaining offers, the score is awarded according to the formula:
P4(n) = (%_minimum offered / %_n) × 15, where:
P4(n): the score obtained by the admissible offer under evaluation;
%_minimum offered = the lowest energy consumption expressed in kWh/100 km offered;
%_n = the offered value.

column3:
Extindere perioada garanție: Durata minima a garantiei de buna executie este de 3 ani. Pentru o durata a garantiei mai mica decat durata minim acceptata de 3 ani, oferta va fi declarata neconforma.
Extinderea duratei de garantie se face cu adaugarea unui an intreg (ex:3 ani + 1 an=4 ani, 3 ani + 2 ani = 5 ani), Punctajul pentru Garantia extinsa a produselor se acorda astfel:
0 (zero) puncte pentru garantia minima de 3 ani;
5 (cinci) puncte pentru extinderea duratei de garantie de la 3 ani la 4 ani, respectiv pentru un an de extra-garantie;
10 (zece) puncte pentru extinderea duratei de garantie de la 3 ani la 5 ani, respectiv pentru doi ani de extra-garantie ;
Nu se acorda punctaj intermediar pentru intervale mai mici de 12 luni. Pentru ofertele care aloca o garantie a produselor peste 5 ani se va acorda punctajul maxim alocat de 10 puncte.

column4:
Extension of warranty period: The minimum duration of the performance guarantee is 3 years. For a warranty period shorter than the minimum accepted duration of 3 years, the offer will be declared non‑conforming.
The extension of the warranty period is done by adding a whole year (e.g., 3 years + 1 year = 4 years, 3 years + 2 years = 5 years). The scoring for extended product warranty is awarded as follows:
0 (zero) points for the minimum warranty of 3 years;
5 (five) points for extending the warranty from 3 years to 4 years, i.e., for one extra‑year of guarantee;
10 (ten) points for extending the warranty from 3 years to 5 years, i.e., for two extra‑years of guarantee;
No intermediate points are awarded for intervals of less than 12 months. For offers that allocate a product warranty beyond 5 years, the maximum score of 10 points will be awarded.

column3:
Ambalaj din material reciclat: Ofertantul va prezenta o declarație oficială din partea producătorului echipamentului privind ambalajul produselor, în care va preciza proporția de material reciclat.

Pentru calculularea proporției de material reciclat aferentă ofertei, se va nota procentajul de material reciclat pentru fiecare produs în parte și se va calcula media ponderată în funcție de cantitatea totală solicitată a fiecărui produs.

Alegerea acestui factor de evaluare a avut următoarele considerente:
-   Reducerea impactului asupra mediului, utilizarea ambalajelor reciclabile ajutând la reducerea cantităților de deșeuri;
-   Respectarea de către producătorii echipamentelor a reglementărilor legale și standardelor de mediu .
Algoritm de calcul pentru ambalaj reciclat:
a) Pentru o proporție de material reciclat de până la 5 0% se vor acorda 0 puncte; 
b) Pentru o proporție de material reciclat cuprinsă între 51% și 70% se vor acorda 10 puncte; 
c) Pentru o proporție de material reciclat cuprinsă între 71% și 100% se vor acorda 20 puncte.

column4:
Recycled material packaging: The bidder shall provide an official statement from the equipment manufacturer regarding the product packaging, indicating the proportion of recycled material.

For calculating the proportion of recycled material applicable to the offer, the percentage of recycled material for each product shall be recorded and a weighted average shall be calculated based on the total quantity requested for each product.

The choice of this evaluation factor had the following considerations:
- Reducing environmental impact, using recyclable packaging helps reduce waste quantities;
- Compliance by equipment manufacturers with legal regulations and environmental standards.

Calculation algorithm for recycled packaging:
a) For a recycled material proportion up to 50% zero points shall be awarded;
b) For a proportion between 51% and 70% ten points shall be awarded;
c) For a proportion between 71% and 100% twenty points shall be awarded.

PACKAGING FROM RECYCLED MATERIAL: Technical component, according to Article 3 of Directive 94/62/EC of 20 December 1994, "packaging" means:
(a) sales packaging or primary packaging, e.g., packaging designed to constitute a sales unit for the final user or consumer at the point of purchase;
(b) grouped or secondary packaging, e.g., packaging designed to constitute at the point of purchase a grouping including a certain number of sales units, regardless of whether this grouping is sold as such to the user or consumer or serves only as a means of filling shelves at the point of sale; these packages can be separated from the product without affecting its characteristics;
(c) transport or tertiary packaging, e.g., packaging designed to facilitate handling and transport of a number of sales units or grouped packages, with the purpose of preventing physical damage during handling and transport. Transport packaging does not include containers used for road, rail, maritime or air transport of goods.
The contracting authority seeks the use of packaging that is fully aligned with environmental conservation and development, i.e., primary packaging as defined in Directive 94/62/EC, amended by Directive 2004/12/EC.
Packaging must be made of easily recyclable materials and/or materials obtained from renewable sources. All packaging materials must be easily separable by hand into recyclable components made of a single type of material (e.g., cardboard, paper, plastic, textile material).
In cases where cartons and/or plastic bags or films are used for product packaging:
- cardboard boxes must contain at least 50% recycled material;
- plastic bags or films for final packaging must contain at least 50% recycled material or be biodegradable or compostable, in accordance with the definition provided in EN 13432.
Products that bear a relevant Type I ecological label meet this requirement. Alternatively, a declaration of conformity with this packaging criterion is submitted. The criterion applies only to primary packaging as defined in Directive 94/62/EC.

Scoring algorithm:
a) The offer with the highest proportion of recycled material receives the maximum score, i.e., 20 points;
b) For the remaining offers the score P(n) is awarded as follows:

P(4) = (Parn/Parmax) × 20 points
Where:
P(4) – score for the admissible, scored offer;
Parn – proportion of recyclable packaging in the admissible, scored offer;
Parmax – highest proportion of recyclable packaging offered among admissible offers.

Verification: A description of the product packaging is submitted with the note that the contracting authority will ensure that delivered products are accompanied by documentation from the manufacturer confirming the percentage of recycled material used in the packaging. Products bearing a relevant Type I ecological label meet this requirement.
Offers that do not certify at the submission deadline that they meet the above requirement will receive 0 points.

