column3:
2.   Termenul de livrare al produselor (P2): Componenta tehnică, Punctajul se acorda astfel:
a) Pentru cel mai scazut dintre termene se acorda punctajul maxim alocat;
b) Pentru celelalte termene ofertate punctajul T(n) se calculeaza proportional, astfel: T(n) = (Termen minim ofertat / Termen n) x punctaj maxim alocat

column4:
2. Delivery term of the products (P2): Technical component, the score is awarded as follows:
a) For the shortest among the terms, the maximum allocated score is awarded;
b) For the other offered terms, the score T(n) is calculated proportionally, as: T(n) = (Minimum offered term / Term n) * maximum allocated score

Delivery time of the products: Delivery time of the products: Maximum score of 10 points (10% weight of the final score), the calculation algorithm for the evaluation factor "delivery time" is granted as follows:
- for economic operators with a product delivery time of 3 days the offer is considered compliant;
- for economic operators with a product delivery time greater than 3 days the offer is considered non‑compliant;
- for a delivery time of 1 day the product score will be maximal, i.e., 10 points.
For offers with product delivery times between 1 day and 3 days the score will be awarded as follows:
a) For the shortest product delivery time the maximum score allocated to that evaluation factor is granted;
b) For any other product delivery time than the one provided in point a) the score is calculated proportionally as:
TLnominal = (TLmin / TL nominal) × 10 points.
Legend: TLmin = minimum delivery time, awarded to the offer with the shortest delivery time;
TL nominal = delivery time offered by the economic operator for which the score is calculated.
The product delivery time shall be mentioned in Annex Form 11 (Technical proposal annex).
Note: According to art. 3 lit. ddd) of Law 98/2016 "days – calendar days, except where expressly stated that they are working days". If the delivery time is expressed in working days, the contracting authority will declare the offer non‑compliant without requesting further clarifications.

column3:
Numarul de showroom-uri in Bucuresti: Numarul de showroom-uri in Bucuresti    -  Punctajul maxim de 10 puncte (10% pondere din punctajul final), Punctajul pentru factorul de evaluare ”Numarul de showroom-uri in Bucuresti” se acorda astfel :
•pentru operatorii economici cu un singur showroom in Bucuresti  oferta este considerata conforma ;
•pentru operatorii economici cu nici un showroom in Bucuresti oferta este considerata neconforma ;
Pentru ofertele cu mai mult de un showroom in Bucuresti  punctajul se va acorda astfel :
a) Pentru cel mai mare numar de showroom-uri in Bucuresti  se acordă punctajul maxim alocat factorului de evaluare respectiv;
b) Pentru alt nr. de showroom-uri din Bucuresti  prevăzut la lit a) se calculeaza proportional astfel:
TG nominal= (TG nominal / TG max) x 10 pct. 
Legenda: 
TG max = nr. de showroom-uri din Bucuresti se acorda  pentru  operatorul cu cele mai multe showroom-uri 
TG nominal = numarul de showroom-uri din Bucuresti pentru care se calculeaza punctajul.

column4:
Number of showrooms in Bucharest: Number of showrooms in Bucharest – maximum score of 10 points (10% weight of the final score). The score for the evaluation factor “Number of showrooms in Bucharest” is awarded as follows:
• For economic operators with a single showroom in Bucharest, the offer is considered compliant;
• For economic operators with no showroom in Bucharest, the offer is considered non‑compliant;
For offers with more than one showroom in Bucharest, the score is awarded as follows:
a) The operator with the highest number of showrooms in Bucharest receives the maximum points allocated to this evaluation factor;
b) For any other number of showrooms in Bucharest, the score is calculated proportionally as:
Nominal TG = (Nominal TG / TG max) × 10 points.
Legend:
TG max = number of showrooms in Bucharest assigned to the operator with the most showrooms;
TG nominal = number of showrooms in Bucharest for which the points are calculated.

column3:
P8: Ambalaje de livrare reciclabile: Componenta tehnica, Autoritatea contractantă urmăreşte utilizarea de ambalaje care să fie în deplină corelaţie cu conservarea şi dezvoltarea mediului, respectiv ambalaje primare astfel cum sunt definite în Directiva 94/62/CE, modificată prin Directiva 2004/12/CE.
Algoritm de calcul:
a) Pentru o proporţie de material reciclat de până la 50% se vor acorda 3 puncte;
b) Pentru o proporţie de material reciclat cuprinsă între 51% și 70% se vor acorda 5 puncte;
c) Pentru o proporţie de material reciclat cuprinsă între 71% și 100% se vor acorda 10 puncte;
Modalitatea de verificare:
Ofertanţii vor prezenta o declaraţie privind ambalajul produselor, în care va declara proporţia de material reciclat. Aceasta va fi însoţită de documente provenite de la producător, traduse de un traducător autorizat în limba română, care confirmă procentul de material reciclat folosit la ambalaj.
Notă:
Pentru ofertele care nu vor furniza informaţiile justificative se va acorda punctaj 0!

column4:
P8: Recyclable delivery packaging: Technical component, the contracting authority seeks the use of packaging that is fully aligned with environmental conservation and development, i.e., primary packaging as defined in Directive 94/62/EC, amended by Directive 2004/12/EC.
Calculation algorithm:
a) For a recycled material proportion up to 50% – 3 points;
b) For a recycled material proportion between 51% and 70% – 5 points;
c) For a recycled material proportion between 71% and 100% – 10 points;
Verification method:
Bidders shall submit a declaration regarding the product packaging, stating the proportion of recycled material. This shall be accompanied by documents from the manufacturer, translated by an authorized translator into Romanian, confirming the percentage of recycled material used in the packaging.
Note:
For offers that do not provide the supporting information, a score of 0 will be awarded.

