Extension of the warranty period: The minimum duration of the performance guarantee is 3 years. For a guarantee period shorter than the minimum accepted duration of 3 years, the offer will be declared non‑conforming.
The extension of the guarantee period is done by adding a whole year (e.g., 3 years + 1 year = 4 years, 3 years + 2 years = 5 years). Calculation algorithm:
The score for the extended product warranty is awarded as follows:
0 (zero) points for the minimum 3‑year guarantee;
5 (five) points for extending the guarantee period from 3 years to 4 years, i.e., for one extra year of guarantee;
10 (ten) points for extending the guarantee period from 3 years to 5 years, i.e., for two extra years of guarantee;
No intermediate points are awarded for intervals shorter than 12 months. For offers that allocate a product guarantee of more than 5 years, the maximum score of 10 points will be awarded.

