Oferta este declarată neconformă în cazul în care contractantul nu dispune de minim un Manager de contract și/sau Coordonator contract și/sau Adjunct manager de contract și/sau Adjunct Coordonator de contract sau poziții echivalente cu acestea, conform solicitării, care să fi participat la implementarea a cel puțin unui proiect/contract similar.
Pentru demonstrarea încadrării în una din situațiile de mai sus, în cadrul ofertei tehnice, se va prezenta: 
-CV-ul – semnat de titular, din care să rezulte experienţa profesională; 
-Documente justificative care demonstreaza pregatirea profesionala (diplome/ certificate/adeverinte/etc), sau echivalent pentru cetăţenii din alte ţări; 
-Declaraţie de disponibilitate, semnată de titular;
-Recomandare/Document constatator emis de Beneficiar din care să rezulte clar numele proiectului/contractului, calitatea specialistului nominalizat pe care a avut-o în derularea proiectului/contractului (Sef de proiect sau echivalent sau poziții echivalente cu acestea ca responsabilități) și calitatea serviciilor prestate de către acesta. Pentru personalul nerezident se acceptă prezentarea certificatelor/autorizațiilor corespunzătoare emise în țara de rezidență.

Aplicarea criteriului de atribuire se face doar ofertelor care respectă toate cerințele din caietul de sarcini. Daca in urma aplicarii criteriului de atribuire: „cel mai bun raport calitate-pret”, două sau mai multe oferte sunt clasate pe primul loc, cu punctaje egale, departajarea se va face având în vedere punctajul obţinut la factorii de evaluare în ordinea descrescătoare a ponderilor acestora. În situaţia în care egalitatea se menţine, autoritatea contractantă are dreptul sa solicite noi propuneri financiare, iar oferta câştigătoare va fi desemnată cea cu propunerea financiară cea mai mică.

column4:
Experience held by the Project Manager: By "Experience held by the Project Manager" is meant the experience held as project manager or equivalent positions with similar responsibilities, in contracts whose object is public/civil construction works, i.e., construction/rehabilitation/modernisation/expansion of buildings, similar or more complex/valuable, at least falling in the minimum importance category C, according to the provisions of Government Decision no. 766/1997 updated, whose beneficiaries are contracting authorities or private clients. 
Scoring for the evaluation factor "Experience held by the Project Manager" (or equivalent) is assigned based on placement in one of the following situations:
- For participation as Project Manager or equivalent in the execution of 6 (six) or more similar contracts, the maximum score for the evaluation factor is awarded, i.e., 30 points;
- For participation as Project Manager or equivalent in the execution of 4‑5 similar contracts, 20 points are awarded;
- For participation as Project Manager or equivalent in the execution of 2‑3 similar contracts, 10 points are awarded;
- For participation as a Engineer specialised in industrial/civil construction, or equivalent, in the execution of 1 similar contract, 0 points are awarded.
An offer is declared non‑conforming if the contractor does not have at least one Contract Manager and/or Contract Coordinator and/or Deputy Contract Manager and/or Deputy Coordinator, or equivalent positions as requested, who have participated in at least one similar project/contract.
To demonstrate compliance with one of the above situations, the technical offer must include:
- The CV (signed by the holder) showing professional experience;
- Supporting documents proving professional qualification (diplomas/certificates/ attestations, etc.) or equivalent for citizens of other countries;
- A declaration of availability, signed by the holder;
- A recommendation / confirmation document issued by the Beneficiary clearly stating the name of the project/contract, the role of the nominated specialist (Project Manager or equivalent or equivalent responsibilities) and the quality of services provided. For non‑resident personnel, certificates/authorisations issued in the country of residence are accepted.

The award criterion is applied only to offers that meet all the requirements of the specifications. If, after applying the "best quality‑price ratio" award criterion, two or more offers rank first with equal scores, the tie‑break is made based on the scores obtained for the evaluation factors in descending order of their weightings. If equality persists, the contracting authority may request new financial proposals, and the winning offer will be the one with the lowest financial proposal.

