For bidders who do not own any electric and/or hybrid machines, the offer will be declared compliant and scored with 0.01 points (the minimum score allowed by the system). Bidders must submit identity cards/registration certificates showing the propulsion system. Bidders must provide supporting documents that prove/confirm how they have possession or access to the machines, such as contracts/invoice purchases/delivery‑acceptance protocols, registration certificates, identity cards, lease contracts, loan agreements or other equivalent documents from which the necessary information can be derived for the appropriate scoring.
