Management of construction site waste: ecological component, points are awarded as follows:
- For the offer with the highest number of concrete measures proposed to reduce the amount of waste produced during the execution of construction works, the maximum allocated points, i.e., 15 points, are awarded;
- For the other offers, the points are calculated proportionally as:
   P points (n) = P measures (n) / P measures (max) × 15 (maximum allocated points), where:
P points (n) – the points obtained by the admissible offer evaluated for the evaluation factor “Management of construction site waste”;
P measures (n) – the number of concrete measures proposed to reduce the amount of waste produced during the execution of construction works and documented within the admissible offer under evaluation;
P measures (max) – the highest number of concrete measures proposed to reduce the amount of waste produced during the execution of construction works and documented within the admissible offers.
The application of the evaluation factor will be carried out only for measures proposed in addition to the minimum requirements in the Terms of Reference, specified in Chapter 5.3 Results to be achieved by the Contractor, 2. Execution.

